## Implementation Approach by Complexity Level

### Level 1: Simple Fix Implementation

For simple bug fixes, typo corrections, or minor improvements:

<mermaid>
graph TD
    L1["Level 1<br>Implementation"] --> L1Review["Review Issue"]
    L1Review --> L1Locate["Locate Affected Code"]
    L1Locate --> L1Fix["Implement Fix"]
    L1Fix --> L1Test["Test Fix"]
    L1Test --> L1Doc["Document Fix"]
    
    style L1 fill:#4dbb5f,stroke:#36873f,color:white
    style L1Review fill:#d6f5dd,stroke:#a3e0ae
    style L1Locate fill:#d6f5dd,stroke:#a3e0ae
    style L1Fix fill:#d6f5dd,stroke:#a3e0ae
    style L1Test fill:#d6f5dd,stroke:#a3e0ae
    style L1Doc fill:#d6f5dd,stroke:#a3e0ae
</mermaid>

**Key Activities**:
- Identify the precise location of the issue
- Make minimal, targeted changes
- Verify the fix resolves the issue
- Add appropriate unit tests
- Update documentation if necessary

**Example Commands**:
```bash
# Find relevant code
grep -r "function_with_bug" src/

# Run specific test
pytest tests/path/to/test_file.py::test_specific_function -v

# Verify fix
pytest tests/path/to/test_file.py
```

### Level 2: Feature Enhancement Implementation

For adding new features or enhancing existing functionality:

<mermaid>
graph TD
    L2["Level 2<br>Implementation"] --> L2Plan["Review Design Plan"]
    L2Plan --> L2Structure["Create Structure"]
    L2Structure --> L2Implement["Implement Core Logic"]
    L2Implement --> L2Edge["Handle Edge Cases"]
    L2Edge --> L2Unit["Write Unit Tests"]
    L2Unit --> L2Integration["Integration Testing"]
    L2Integration --> L2Doc["Update Documentation"]
    
    style L2 fill:#ffa64d,stroke:#cc7a30,color:white
    style L2Plan fill:#ffe6cc,stroke:#ffa64d
    style L2Structure fill:#ffe6cc,stroke:#ffa64d
    style L2Implement fill:#ffe6cc,stroke:#ffa64d
    style L2Edge fill:#ffe6cc,stroke:#ffa64d
    style L2Unit fill:#ffe6cc,stroke:#ffa64d
    style L2Integration fill:#ffe6cc,stroke:#ffa64d
    style L2Doc fill:#ffe6cc,stroke:#ffa64d
</mermaid>

**Key Activities**:
- Review the feature design thoroughly
- Create the basic structure or scaffolding
- Implement the core functionality
- Address edge cases and error conditions
- Write comprehensive unit tests
- Perform integration testing
- Update technical and user documentation

**Example Commands**:
```bash
# Create feature branch
git checkout -b feature/new-enhancement

# Format code
black src/path/to/implementation/

# Run linting
pylint src/path/to/implementation/

# Run tests with coverage
pytest --cov=src/path/to/implementation tests/path/to/tests/
```

